td.paragraph: The patient experiences recurrent
episodes concerning for sustained
arrhythmia, possibly atrial fibrillation versus SVT. Prior event monitors and echocardiograms
have been negative for atrial
fibrillation. She is currently not
on any antiarrhythmic medication or anticoagulant. We will proceed with pre-authorization for a one-week outpatient
event monitor. Consider loop
recorder implantation if clinically indicated to rule out atrial fibrillation. Given the frequency of episodes, EKG monitoring should help diagnose a rhythm
disturbance. The patient will maintain
a symptom diary with associated vital signs until further testing is
completed.
